### Hyperspace API Tests
# If you are using VS Code, you can install the "REST Client" extension
# by Huachao Mao to run these requests directly from this file!

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8787
@email = testuser@example.com
@password = supersecret123

### 1. Check Server Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{email}}",
    "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Login to get JWT Token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{email}}",
    "password": "{{password}}"
}

### -> NOTE: Copy the "token" from the login response and paste it below
@authToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiI3Y2NmZmI2Zi04YTBhLTQ2YTMtODNhZC00ODI3OWI1MWI2ZmQiLCJleHAiOjE3ODMzNDI3NDZ9.qdJMVVPaTYOxznQiDyTsvEyVeP3CibvMiVbrZ4q77h8

### 4. Create a Private Journal Entry
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/entries
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "content": "This is my very first journal entry! I'm building Hyperspace.",
    "is_public": true,
    "mood": "excited",
    "location": "Earth"
}

### 5. Fetch all my Private Entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/entries
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Fetch Public Entries (Website view)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/public/entries
